    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Create a new instance to handle XML-RPC requests in a CGI environment. The allow_none and encoding parameters are passed on to xmlrpc.client and control the XML-RPC responses that will be returned from the server. The use_builtin_types parameter is passed to the loads() function and controls which types are processed when date/times values or binary data are received; it defaults to false. Changed in version 3.3: The use_builtin_types flag was added."
